x4freetext: n TOF facility .
Spallation reaction induced by 20 GeV/c protons
onto solid lead target.Time resolution of proton beam
6ns (r.m.s.), intensity up to 7.E+12 proton/pulse.
Flight distance 184.9+-0.1 m .
108 mg of U3-O8 (91 mg of U, 0.356 MBq), pressed in
pellet and doubly encapsulated between Al and Ti foils
of 0.15 mm and 0.2 mm thick respectively.
Isotopic purity(determined by gamma-ray spectroscopy):
Targets are placed at the center of the TAC and
surrounded by neutron absorber of C12-H20-O4(Li-6)2.
U-233 thickness 2.994E-4 at/b was used to convert
yields into cross-sections.
Total gamma ray Absorption Calorimeter
,TAC, is 4PI detector , based on 40 BaF2 crystals
shaped as hexagonal and pentagonal pyramids forming
spherical shell with 10 cm inner radius and 15 cm
thickness. Each BaF2 is covered by teflon light
reflector layer, an aluminum foil and a final cover
with B-10 loaded carbon fiber capsule.
Detection efficiency for capture events near 100%.
Acceptable energy resolution of 10% at 661.5 keV tp
6% at 6.15 MeV.
Neutron absorber as the B-10 loaded carbon fiber.
Between two energy calibration, the energy drift is
monitored by using the intrinsic radioactivity of BaF2
crystals.
Shape analysis of the TAC energy response for
each time-of-flight (neutron energy) bin.
4.5 eV resonance was used to define fission.
Efficiency for capture was defined by simulation
consisted in gamma-ray cascade generator coupled to
GEANT4 toolkit.
The overall normalization coefficient for both capture
and fission data was obtained by assuming a 100%
efficiency detection for fission with the considered
event selection criteria (i.e. more than one cluster
in the TAC). Since the data are normalized to n TOF &
ORELA fission data and since the fission detection
efficiency is more likely around 85%, one can expect
a capture cross section about 15% lower than these
presents data (since these number are only rough guess
these values should stay "out of the record").
Above 100 eV, the capture/fission discrimination
clearly need some improvements since the fission seems
systematically higher than n TOF & ORELA data, giving
certainly an underestimation of the capture cross
section in this range.
Contribution only of U-234 was subtracted.
For background.
For self-shielding effect taking elastic cross section
from ENDF/B-VII evaluation.
Berthoumieux, 08 Sept.2009.
M.M.
These data were obtained by normalizing on ORELA and
on n-TOF measurements. Obtained normalization factor
was used to deduce the capture cross section.
